research_municipality_step.notes: Austin, TX operates under a council-manager form of government, which is a variation of the mayor-council system. The Mayor is elected at large, and ten Council Members are elected from single-member districts. Vanessa Fuentes also serves as Mayor Pro Tem. The information for District 6 and 10 reflects the results of the November 2024 elections where Krista Laine unseated Mackenzie Kelly and Marc Duchen won against Ashika Ganguly.
